\v 16 \w Every|strong="H3605"\w* \w time|strong="H5769"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w look|strong="H7200"\w* \w at|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w rainbow|strong="H7198"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w clouds|strong="H6051"\w*, \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w remember|strong="H2142"\w* \w what|strong="H7200"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* promised \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w*, \w and|strong="H5769"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w animals|strong="H2416"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* earth. \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w never|strong="H5769"\w* break \w that|strong="H7200"\w* \w promise|strong="H1285"\w*. \w It|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w last|strong="H5769"\w* \w for|strong="H5921"\w* \w ever|strong="H5769"\w*.”   
\p
\v 17 \w And|strong="H6965"\w* God said \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w Noah|strong="H5146"\w*, “\w This|strong="H2063"\w* \w is|strong="H3605"\w* very important. \w That|strong="H3605"\w* rainbow \w will|strong="H1320"\w* \w help|strong="H6965"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* remember \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w myself|strong="H1320"\w* promised \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w for|strong="H5921"\w* \w every|strong="H3605"\w* \w living|strong="H1320"\w* \w thing|strong="H2063"\w*.”   
\s1 Noah got drunk  
\p
\v 18-19 Noah had 3 sons. Their names were Shem, and Ham, and Jafeth. They were on the boat with Noah, and after they got off the boat, they had their own sons and daughters. One of Ham’s sons was called Canaan, and there were lots of other sons and daughters too. And later, all those kids had more kids, and it kept going like that. All the people in the world are from Noah’s family.   
\p
\v 20 Soon after \w Noah|strong="H5146"\w* came out \w of|strong="H3754"\w* \w the|strong="H2490"\w* big boat, \w he|strong="H5146"\w* \w started|strong="H2490"\w* growing \w a|strong="H3068"\w* garden. \w He|strong="H5146"\w* \w planted|strong="H5193"\w* some grape \w vines|strong="H3754"\w*, \w and|strong="H3754"\w* \w they|strong="H2490"\w* grew some \w grapes|strong="H2490"\w*. \w Then|strong="H2490"\w* \w he|strong="H5146"\w* made some wine \w from|strong="H3754"\w* those \w grapes|strong="H2490"\w*.  
\v 21 Noah \w drank|strong="H8354"\w* \w some|strong="H4480"\w* \w of|strong="H4480"\w* \w that|strong="H4480"\w* \w wine|strong="H3196"\w* \w and|strong="H8354"\w* got \w drunk|strong="H8354"\w*. \w He|strong="H4480"\w* took \w his|strong="H1540"\w* clothes \w off|strong="H4480"\w* \w and|strong="H8354"\w* \w went|strong="H1540"\w* \w to|strong="H1540"\w* sleep \w in|strong="H8432"\w* \w his|strong="H1540"\w* tent.  
\v 22 \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w* (\w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w*’s father) \w went|strong="H8147"\w* \w into|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* tent \w and|strong="H7200"\w* \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* \w his|strong="H7200"\w* naked father. \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w* didn’t \w respect|strong="H7200"\w* \w his|strong="H7200"\w* father, \w so|strong="H7200"\w* \w he|strong="H8147"\w* \w went|strong="H8147"\w* \w outside|strong="H2351"\w* \w and|strong="H7200"\w* \w told|strong="H5046"\w* \w his|strong="H7200"\w* brothers \w what|strong="H7200"\w* happened.  
\v 23 \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* Jafeth \w got|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* coat. \w They|strong="H5921"\w* held \w it|strong="H7760"\w* \w over|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H3947"\w* \w shoulders|strong="H7926"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w walked|strong="H3212"\w* backwards \w into|strong="H3212"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* tent. \w They|strong="H5921"\w* \w put|strong="H7760"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* coat \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H3947"\w* father \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w cover|strong="H3680"\w* \w his|strong="H7760"\w* naked body. \w They|strong="H5921"\w* didn’t \w turn|strong="H7760"\w* \w around|strong="H5921"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w look|strong="H7200"\w* \w at|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H3947"\w* naked father.   
\p
\v 24 After \w Noah|strong="H5146"\w* \w woke|strong="H3364"\w* \w up|strong="H6213"\w*, \w he|strong="H6213"\w* \w found|strong="H3045"\w* \w out|strong="H6213"\w* \w what|strong="H3045"\w* Ham, \w his|strong="H3045"\w* \w youngest|strong="H6996"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w*, \w did|strong="H6213"\w* \w to|strong="H6213"\w* \w him|strong="H6213"\w*.  
\v 25 \w Then|strong="H1961"\w* Noah said, “\w I|strong="H5650"\w*’m going \w to|strong="H1961"\w* curse \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w*, Ham’s son. He \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w have|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* work hard \w for|strong="H5650"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* relatives, \w without|strong="H1961"\w* pay.  
\v 26 \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* good. \w I|strong="H5650"\w*’m going \w to|strong="H3068"\w* ask \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w look|strong="H3068"\w* \w after|strong="H1961"\w* \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w*, \w but|strong="H1961"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* work hard \w for|strong="H3068"\w* \w him|strong="H1288"\w* \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w no|strong="H1961"\w* pay.  
\v 27 \w I|strong="H5650"\w*’m going \w to|strong="H1961"\w* ask God \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w give|strong="H1961"\w* Jafeth \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big country. Jafeth \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* share \w that|strong="H5650"\w* country, \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* work hard \w for|strong="H5650"\w* \w them|strong="H1961"\w* \w with|strong="H1961"\w* \w no|strong="H1961"\w* pay.”   
\p
\v 28 \w Noah|strong="H5146"\w* \w lived|strong="H2421"\w* \w for|strong="H2421"\w* another 350 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w after|strong="H8141"\w* \w the|strong="H2421"\w* \w flood|strong="H3999"\w*.  
\v 29 \w He|strong="H3117"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w* \w when|strong="H1961"\w* \w he|strong="H3117"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* 950 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w old|strong="H8141"\w*.   
\c 10  
\s1 The story about Noah’s sons and their families  
\p
\v 1 \w This|strong="H1121"\w* \w is|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* story about \w Noah|strong="H5146"\w*’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* their \w families|strong="H1121"\w*. \w His|strong="H3205"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* Jafeth, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* after \w that|strong="H1121"\w* big \w flood|strong="H3999"\w*, \w they|strong="H3205"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w* \w kids|strong="H1121"\w* too.   
\s1 The tribes from Jafeth’s family  
\p
\v 2-5 \w A|strong="H3068"\w* long time later, the people that were born into Jafeth’s family split up into different tribes and nations. Each tribe had their own language, and their own country. Jafeth’s sons were Gomer, and Magog, and Madayi, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshek, and Tiras.  
\p The tribes that were from Jafeth’s son Gomer and his family were the Ashkenaz mob, and the Rifath mob, and the Togarmah mob.  
\p The tribes that were from Jafeth’s son Javan and his family were the Elishah mob, and the Tarshish mob, and the Kit mob, and the Rodan mob.  
\p Javan’s people lived near the sea.   
\s1 The tribes from Ham’s family  
\p
\v 6 \w The|strong="H1121"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w that|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w born|strong="H1121"\w* \w into|strong="H4714"\w* \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w*’s family split \w up|strong="H1121"\w* \w into|strong="H4714"\w* different tribes too, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* each tribe \w had|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H4714"\w* own language, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H4714"\w* own country. \w Ham|strong="H2526"\w*’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w Cush|strong="H3568"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Put|strong="H6316"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w*.   
\p
\v 7 \w The|strong="H1121"\w* tribes \w that|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* Ham’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w Cush|strong="H3568"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H1121"\w* family \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Seba|strong="H5434"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Havilah|strong="H2341"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Sabtah|strong="H5454"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* Ramah mob, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Sabteca|strong="H5455"\w* mob. \w And|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* tribes \w that|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* Ramah \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H1121"\w* family \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Sheba|strong="H7614"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w Dedan|strong="H1719"\w* mob.   
\p
