\c 11  
\s1 People tried to build a tall building  
\p
\v 1 \w You|strong="H3605"\w* know, \w at|strong="H1961"\w* first \w everyone|strong="H3605"\w* talked \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w same|strong="H1697"\w* \w language|strong="H8193"\w*.  
\v 2 \w And|strong="H8033"\w* \w as|strong="H1961"\w* \w people|strong="H3427"\w* \w moved|strong="H5265"\w* \w from|strong="H5265"\w* \w place|strong="H1961"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w place|strong="H1961"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* \w east|strong="H6924"\w*, \w they|strong="H8033"\w* got \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w some|strong="H8033"\w* flat \w country|strong="H6924"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* Babylonia, \w and|strong="H8033"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w stayed|strong="H3427"\w* \w there|strong="H8033"\w*.  
\v 3-4 Then they said to each other, “Look, \w we|strong="H3068"\w* can make bricks here. So come on, let’s do that. We will bake them properly so that they are good strong bricks, and \w we|strong="H3068"\w* will use them to build \w a|strong="H3068"\w* city here. So come on, let’s build \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big tall building in that city. It will be so tall that it will go right up into the sky.” You see, they had bricks and tar instead of stones and cement. And they said, “If \w we|strong="H3068"\w* do that, everyone will think \w we|strong="H3068"\w* are smart. Then \w we|strong="H3068"\w* will not go and live all over the earth, but \w we|strong="H3068"\w* will stay together right here.” \fig The people started to build a really tall building|src="AP-01-40.tif" size="col" ref="11:3-4" \fig*   
\s1 God made people talk in different languages  
\p
\v 5 \w So|strong="H3381"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w started|strong="H1129"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w build|strong="H1129"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w city|strong="H5892"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* really tall \w building|strong="H1129"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w came|strong="H3381"\w* \w down|strong="H3381"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w look|strong="H7200"\w* \w at|strong="H3068"\w* \w those|strong="H1121"\w* things.  
\v 6 \w He|strong="H6213"\w* said, “\w These|strong="H2088"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w can|strong="H6213"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w talk|strong="H8193"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w each|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H2088"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w same|strong="H2088"\w* \w language|strong="H8193"\w*, \w so|strong="H6213"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w can|strong="H6213"\w* \w do|strong="H6213"\w* \w anything|strong="H3605"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w want|strong="H3808"\w*. \w If|strong="H2005"\w* \w they|strong="H1992"\w* \w keep|strong="H6213"\w* \w on|strong="H3068"\w* \w going|strong="H2005"\w* \w this|strong="H2088"\w* \w way|strong="H2088"\w*, \w nothing|strong="H3808"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w stop|strong="H3808"\w* \w them|strong="H1992"\w* \w from|strong="H3068"\w* \w doing|strong="H6213"\w* \w anything|strong="H3605"\w*.  
\v 7 \w Come|strong="H3381"\w* \w on|strong="H8085"\w*, \w let|strong="H3381"\w*’s \w go|strong="H3381"\w* \w down|strong="H3381"\w* \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w these|strong="H8085"\w* \w people|strong="H3808"\w*, \w and|strong="H8085"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w make|strong="H8085"\w* \w them|strong="H3381"\w* \w talk|strong="H8193"\w* \w in|strong="H8085"\w* different languages. \w Then|strong="H8085"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w understand|strong="H8085"\w* each \w other|strong="H7453"\w*, \w and|strong="H8085"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w be|strong="H3808"\w* all \w mixed|strong="H1101"\w* up. \w They|strong="H8033"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* work \w things|strong="H3808"\w* \w out|strong="H3808"\w* \w with|strong="H1101"\w* each \w other|strong="H7453"\w*, \w so|strong="H3808"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w keep|strong="H8085"\w* \w on|strong="H8085"\w* building \w this|strong="H8085"\w* city.”   
\p
\v 8 \w So|strong="H5921"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w made|strong="H1129"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* people talk \w in|strong="H5921"\w* different languages. \w None|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w them|strong="H5921"\w* could understand \w anything|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* people \w were|strong="H5892"\w* saying. \w So|strong="H5921"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w stopped|strong="H2308"\w* \w building|strong="H1129"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* big \w city|strong="H5892"\w*.  
\v 9 \w They|strong="H3588"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w left|strong="H8033"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* city \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w went|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w live|strong="H8034"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* lots \w of|strong="H3068"\w* different \w places|strong="H3605"\w*, \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w over|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* world. \w That|strong="H3588"\w*’s \w how|strong="H3588"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* got people \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w be|strong="H3068"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* different tribes \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w over|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* world. \w And|strong="H3068"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w called|strong="H7121"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* city \em Babel\em*. \w That|strong="H3588"\w* \w means|strong="H3651"\w* \em mixed up\em*. \w They|strong="H3588"\w* \w gave|strong="H7121"\w* \w it|strong="H7121"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w mixed|strong="H1101"\w* \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* languages \w at|strong="H5921"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w time|strong="H6440"\w*. \fig God made people talk different languages so they didn’t understand each other|src="lll1-08.tif" size="col" ref="11:9" \fig*   
\s1 The story of Shem’s family  
\p
\v 10 \w This|strong="H1121"\w* \w is|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* story about \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w*’s family.\x * \xo 11:10 \xt Genesis 10:21; Luke 3:35-36\x*  
\p \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w* \w was|strong="H1121"\w* 100 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w old|strong="H1121"\w* \w when|strong="H1121"\w* \w he|strong="H8141"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* called Arfaxad. \w That|strong="H8141"\w* \w was|strong="H1121"\w* 2 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w after|strong="H8141"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* big \w flood|strong="H3999"\w*.  
\v 11 \w Shem|strong="H8035"\w* \w lived|strong="H2421"\w* \w for|strong="H1121"\w* 500 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w after|strong="H8141"\w* \w he|strong="H2568"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w* Arfaxad, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w he|strong="H2568"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w* \w more|strong="H3205"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w daughters|strong="H1323"\w*.   
\p
