\c 12  
\s1 God picked Abram  
\p
\v 1 \w This|strong="H7200"\w* story \w about|strong="H1004"\w* Abram started \w when|strong="H7200"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* said \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w him|strong="H7200"\w*, “Abram, \w I|strong="H7200"\w* want \w you|strong="H7200"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* leave \w your|strong="H3068"\w* country, \w your|strong="H3068"\w* father’s \w family|strong="H1004"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w all|strong="H7200"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w relatives|strong="H4138"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w go|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* country \w that|strong="H7200"\w* \w I|strong="H7200"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w show|strong="H7200"\w* \w you|strong="H7200"\w*.\x * \xo 12:1 \xt Acts 7:2-4; Hebrews 11:8\x*  
\v 2 \w And|strong="H1419"\w* \w I|strong="H1961"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w give|strong="H6213"\w* \w you|strong="H6213"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w big|strong="H1431"\w* family, \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w they|strong="H6213"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w become|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w great|strong="H1419"\w* \w nation|strong="H1471"\w*, \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w I|strong="H1961"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w do|strong="H6213"\w* good \w things|strong="H1419"\w* \w for|strong="H6213"\w* \w you|strong="H6213"\w* \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w your|strong="H6213"\w* family, \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w I|strong="H1961"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w make|strong="H6213"\w* \w your|strong="H6213"\w* mob \w strong|strong="H1419"\w*. \w Then|strong="H1961"\w* everyone \w will|strong="H1961"\w* know \w about|strong="H1961"\w* \w you|strong="H6213"\w* \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w your|strong="H6213"\w* family, \w and|strong="H1419"\w* everyone \w will|strong="H1961"\w* respect \w you|strong="H6213"\w*. \w And|strong="H1419"\w* \w you|strong="H6213"\w* \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w your|strong="H6213"\w* family \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w do|strong="H6213"\w* good \w things|strong="H1419"\w* \w for|strong="H6213"\w* other \w people|strong="H1471"\w*.  
\v 3 \w If|strong="H7043"\w* \w anyone|strong="H3605"\w* does good \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w and|strong="H3605"\w* \w your|strong="H3605"\w* \w family|strong="H4940"\w*, \w I|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H3605"\w* \w do|strong="H3605"\w* good \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w them|strong="H1288"\w*. \w But|strong="H3605"\w*, \w if|strong="H7043"\w* \w anyone|strong="H3605"\w* does bad \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w*, \w and|strong="H3605"\w* \w if|strong="H7043"\w* \w they|strong="H3605"\w* \w make|strong="H7043"\w* trouble \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w and|strong="H3605"\w* \w your|strong="H3605"\w* \w family|strong="H4940"\w*, \w I|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H3605"\w* \w curse|strong="H7043"\w* \w them|strong="H1288"\w* \w and|strong="H3605"\w* \w make|strong="H7043"\w* trouble \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w them|strong="H1288"\w*. \w I|strong="H3605"\w* \w will|strong="H3605"\w* use \w your|strong="H3605"\w* \w family|strong="H4940"\w* \w to|strong="H3605"\w* \w do|strong="H3605"\w* good \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w families|strong="H4940"\w* \w in|strong="H4940"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* world.”\x * \xo 12:3 \xt Galatians 3:8\x*   
\s1 Abram and his family went to Canaan country  
\p
\v 4-5 Abram was 75 years old when he left the town called Haran and went to the country called Canaan. That was the country that God told him to go to. He took his wife Sarai, and his nephew Lot with him. He also took all the things and all the workers that they got in Haran, and they all went to the new country called Canaan.  
\v 6 Abram \w and|strong="H4725"\w* everyone \w with|strong="H5674"\w* \w him|strong="H5674"\w* walked \w through|strong="H5674"\w* \w that|strong="H3669"\w* new \w country|strong="H4725"\w*, \w and|strong="H4725"\w* \w they|strong="H5704"\w* \w went|strong="H5674"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town called Shekem, \w and|strong="H4725"\w* \w they|strong="H5704"\w* camped \w there|strong="H5704"\w*, \w near|strong="H5704"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big tree \w at|strong="H5704"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w place|strong="H4725"\w* called \w Moreh|strong="H4176"\w*. \w The|strong="H5704"\w* people \w that|strong="H3669"\w* lived \w in|strong="H4725"\w* \w that|strong="H3669"\w* \w country|strong="H4725"\w* \w were|strong="H7927"\w* called \w the|strong="H5704"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3669"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H4725"\w* \w they|strong="H5704"\w* didn’t know God.\fig Abram and his family camped at Moreh|src="MX-16.tif" size="col" ref="12:6" \fig*  
\v 7 \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w showed|strong="H7200"\w* \w himself|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* Abram \w there|strong="H8033"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* said \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w him|strong="H5414"\w*, “\w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w give|strong="H5414"\w* \w this|strong="H2063"\w* country \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H2233"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w all|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w people|strong="H7200"\w* \w that|strong="H7200"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w be|strong="H3068"\w* born \w into|strong="H5414"\w* \w his|strong="H5414"\w* \w family|strong="H2233"\w* later \w on|strong="H7200"\w*.” \w So|strong="H5414"\w* Abram piled \w up|strong="H5414"\w* stones \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w make|strong="H5414"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* table \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* flat top. \w It|strong="H5414"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* special \w place|strong="H5414"\w* \w for|strong="H3068"\w* \w him|strong="H5414"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* burn animals \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w show|strong="H7200"\w* \w right|strong="H3068"\w* \w respect|strong="H7200"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*.\x * \xo 12:7 \xt Acts 7:5; Galatians 3:16\x* \fig Abram made a special stone table, and he killed animals and burned them on it to show respect to God|src="LB00255b.tif" size="col" ref="12:7" \fig*   
\p
\v 8 \w Later|strong="H5186"\w* \w on|strong="H3068"\w*, Abram \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w his|strong="H3068"\w* mob \w left|strong="H5186"\w* Shekem, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* \w went|strong="H3068"\w* \w south|strong="H3220"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w hill|strong="H2022"\w* \w country|strong="H2022"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w on|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w east|strong="H6924"\w* \w side|strong="H3220"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town \w called|strong="H7121"\w* \w Bethel|strong="H1008"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w they|strong="H8033"\w* camped between \w Bethel|strong="H1008"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* another town \w called|strong="H7121"\w* Ayi. \w Bethel|strong="H1008"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w west|strong="H3220"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w his|strong="H3068"\w* camp \w and|strong="H3068"\w* Ayi \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w east|strong="H6924"\w*. \w Then|strong="H7121"\w* Abram piled \w up|strong="H1129"\w* stones \w there|strong="H8033"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w make|strong="H7121"\w* another special table, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H8033"\w* burned animals \w on|strong="H3068"\w* \w it|strong="H7121"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* show respect \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*. \w He|strong="H8033"\w* \w prayed|strong="H7121"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H8033"\w* \w called|strong="H7121"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w by|strong="H3068"\w* \w his|strong="H3068"\w* special \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \em Yahweh\em*.   
\p
