\s1 Abram and his family went to Egypt country  
\p
\v 10 \w At|strong="H1961"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w time|strong="H1961"\w*, \w there|strong="H8033"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w no|strong="H1961"\w* rain \w and|strong="H4714"\w* \w no|strong="H1961"\w* food plants growing \w in|strong="H1481"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* country. Nobody \w had|strong="H1961"\w* enough food, \w so|strong="H1961"\w* Abram \w and|strong="H4714"\w* everyone \w with|strong="H3381"\w* \w him|strong="H3381"\w* \w went|strong="H3381"\w* south \w to|strong="H3381"\w* \w live|strong="H1481"\w* \w in|strong="H1481"\w* another country, \w called|strong="H8033"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*.  
\v 11 Just \w before|strong="H1961"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* got \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*, Abram said \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w his|strong="H3045"\w* wife \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w*, “\w You|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H4714"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* really \w beautiful|strong="H3303"\w* \w woman|strong="H4758"\w*.  
