\p
\v 5 Abram \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* nephew \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w still|strong="H1980"\w* \w together|strong="H1571"\w*. \w And|strong="H1980"\w* \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w* \w also|strong="H1571"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big mob \w of|strong="H6629"\w* \w sheep|strong="H6629"\w*, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* goats, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w cows|strong="H1241"\w*, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w bulls|strong="H1241"\w*. \w And|strong="H1980"\w* \w he|strong="H1241"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w lot|strong="H3876"\w* \w of|strong="H6629"\w* tents \w for|strong="H1241"\w* \w all|strong="H1571"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* workers \w too|strong="H1571"\w*.  
\v 6-7 But there was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* problem. There were other people already living in that country. They were called the Canaan mob, and the Periz mob. And they had animals too, and all those animals needed grass and water, as well as Abram’s animals, and Lot’s animals too. But there wasn’t enough grass and water in that place for all those animals. So Abram’s work-men and Lot’s work-men started to argue and fight with each other about whose animals got the grass and water.  
\v 8 \w Then|strong="H1961"\w* Abram said \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w*, “\w I|strong="H3588"\w* don’t \w like|strong="H1961"\w* \w this|strong="H3588"\w* trouble. \w You|strong="H3588"\w* \w and|strong="H4994"\w* \w me|strong="H4994"\w*, \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w are|strong="H1961"\w* family, \w and|strong="H4994"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* don’t want trouble between \w us|strong="H4994"\w*. \w And|strong="H4994"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* don’t want \w our|strong="H1961"\w* work-men \w to|strong="H1961"\w* argue \w and|strong="H4994"\w* fight \w with|strong="H1961"\w* each other.  
\v 9 \w Look|strong="H6440"\w*, \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w is|strong="H3605"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lot \w of|strong="H6440"\w* country \w here|strong="H5921"\w*. \w Just|strong="H3605"\w* \w look|strong="H6440"\w* \w around|strong="H5921"\w*, \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* see \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w there|strong="H3605"\w*’s \w plenty|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H6440"\w* country \w for|strong="H5921"\w* \w both|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H6440"\w* \w us|strong="H4994"\w*. \w So|strong="H3808"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* reckon \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w have|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* split \w up|strong="H5921"\w*. \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w want|strong="H3808"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* pick \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w part|strong="H6504"\w* \w of|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* country \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w want|strong="H3808"\w*, \w and|strong="H6440"\w* \w then|strong="H3808"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w go|strong="H8041"\w* somewhere \w else|strong="H3808"\w*. If \w you|strong="H6440"\w* pick \w the|strong="H3605"\w* country \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w east|strong="H5921"\w*, \w then|strong="H3808"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w go|strong="H8041"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* country \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* west, \w but|strong="H3808"\w* if \w you|strong="H6440"\w* pick \w the|strong="H3605"\w* west country, \w then|strong="H3808"\w* \w I|strong="H5921"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w go|strong="H8041"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w east|strong="H5921"\w* country.” \fig Abram told Lot to pick the part of the country he wanted|src="1g Abraham&Lot.tif" size="col" ref="13:9" \fig*   
\p
\v 10 \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w* \w looked|strong="H7200"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w east|strong="H6440"\w*, towards \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town called \w Zoar|strong="H6820"\w*, \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* flat \w country|strong="H3603"\w* \w around|strong="H6440"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w Jordan|strong="H3383"\w* \w River|strong="H3588"\w*. \w He|strong="H3588"\w* \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* flat \w country|strong="H3603"\w* \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w plenty|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* grass \w and|strong="H3068"\w* water. \w It|strong="H3588"\w* \w looked|strong="H7200"\w* \w just|strong="H3605"\w* \w like|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*’s \w garden|strong="H1588"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w like|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w country|strong="H3603"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*. (\w That|strong="H3588"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w burned|strong="H5375"\w* \w up|strong="H5375"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* towns \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* flat \w country|strong="H3603"\w* called \w Sodom|strong="H5467"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w Gomorrah|strong="H6017"\w*.\x * \xo 13:10 \xt Genesis 19:24\x*)  
\v 11-12 So Lot picked the flat country around the Jordan River, to the east.  
\p Then Abram did what he promised, and he went to the country called Canaan.  
\p In that way, Lot’s mob and Abram’s mob went to different places, and there was no more trouble between their work-men.  
\p Lot went to the flat country around the Jordan River. There were some towns there, and Lot camped near the town called Sodom.  
\v 13 \w The|strong="H3068"\w* people \w that|strong="H3068"\w* lived \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w Sodom|strong="H5467"\w* \w were|strong="H5467"\w* \w very|strong="H3966"\w* \w bad|strong="H7451"\w*. \w They|strong="H3068"\w* \w were|strong="H5467"\w* always going \w against|strong="H5467"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w they|strong="H3068"\w* \w did|strong="H3068"\w* \w bad|strong="H7451"\w* \w things|strong="H7451"\w* \w all|strong="H3966"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* time.   
\s1 God made a promise to Abram  
\p
\v 14 \w Then|strong="H5375"\w*, \w after|strong="H4480"\w* \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w* \w left|strong="H4480"\w*, \w God|strong="H3068"\w* said \w to|strong="H3068"\w* Abram, “\w Look|strong="H7200"\w* \w at|strong="H3068"\w* \w all|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w country|strong="H5045"\w* around \w you|strong="H5973"\w*. \w Look|strong="H7200"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w north|strong="H6828"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w south|strong="H5045"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w east|strong="H6924"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* \w west|strong="H3220"\w*.  
\v 15 \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H5414"\w* \w give|strong="H5414"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* country \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w can|strong="H7200"\w* \w see|strong="H7200"\w*. Later \w on|strong="H7200"\w*, \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H5414"\w* \w have|strong="H7200"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H2233"\w*, \w and|strong="H5769"\w* lots \w of|strong="H2233"\w* \w people|strong="H7200"\w* \w will|strong="H5414"\w* \w be|strong="H5769"\w* born \w into|strong="H5414"\w* \w his|strong="H3605"\w* \w family|strong="H2233"\w*, \w and|strong="H5769"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H5414"\w* \w own|strong="H5769"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w this|strong="H5414"\w* country, \w for|strong="H3588"\w* \w ever|strong="H5769"\w*.\x * \xo 13:15 \xt Acts 7:5\x*  
\v 16 \w Look|strong="H7760"\w* \w at|strong="H3201"\w* \w the|strong="H7760"\w* \w ground|strong="H6083"\w* \w you|strong="H7760"\w* \w are|strong="H1571"\w* standing \w on|strong="H7760"\w*, \w it|strong="H7760"\w* \w has|strong="H1571"\w* lots \w of|strong="H2233"\w* little bits \w of|strong="H2233"\w* \w dirt|strong="H6083"\w*. Nobody \w can|strong="H3201"\w* \w count|strong="H4487"\w* \w all|strong="H3201"\w* those little bits \w of|strong="H2233"\w* \w dirt|strong="H6083"\w* \w on|strong="H7760"\w* \w the|strong="H7760"\w* \w ground|strong="H6083"\w*, \w and|strong="H6083"\w* \w just|strong="H1571"\w* \w like|strong="H7760"\w* \w that|strong="H1571"\w*, nobody \w will|strong="H1571"\w* \w be|strong="H1571"\w* \w able|strong="H3201"\w* \w to|strong="H3201"\w* \w count|strong="H4487"\w* \w all|strong="H3201"\w* \w the|strong="H7760"\w* \w people|strong="H1571"\w* \w that|strong="H1571"\w* \w will|strong="H1571"\w* \w be|strong="H1571"\w* \w in|strong="H2233"\w* \w your|strong="H7760"\w* \w family|strong="H2233"\w* later \w on|strong="H7760"\w*.  
