\p
\v 18 \w So|strong="H3427"\w* Abram \w went|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* big trees \w that|strong="H3068"\w* belonged \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* man \w called|strong="H8033"\w* Mamreh, \w near|strong="H8033"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town \w called|strong="H8033"\w* \w Hebron|strong="H2275"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H8033"\w* camped \w there|strong="H8033"\w*. \w He|strong="H8033"\w* piled \w up|strong="H1129"\w* stones \w there|strong="H8033"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w made|strong="H1129"\w* another special table \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* flat top, \w so|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H8033"\w* could burn animals \w to|strong="H3068"\w* show respect \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*.   
\c 14  
\s1 Soldiers grabbed Lot and his family and took them away  
\p
\v 1-9 This story is about the people in the flat country, and it started before Lot went to live near the town called Sodom. There were 5 tribes in that flat country at that time, and each tribe had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* leader. These were the 5 tribes and their leaders,  
\li1 – A tribe called Sodom, and their leader was called Bera.  
\li1 – A tribe called Gomorrah, and their leader was called Birsha.  
\li1 – A tribe called Admah, and their leader was Shinab.  
\li1 – A tribe called the Zebo mob, and their leader was Shemeber.  
\li1 – A tribe called Zoar. They are also called Bela.  
\p There were another 4 tribes in the country to the east. These were those 4 tribes and their leaders,  
\li1 – A tribe called Elam, and their leader was Kedorlayomer.  
\li1 – A tribe called Babylonia, and their leader was called Amrafel.  
\li1 – A tribe called Ellasar, and their leader was called Ariok.  
\li1 – A tribe called the Goy mob, and their leader was Tidal.  
\m And Kedorlayomer was the boss over those 4 tribes in the east. Those 4 tribes sent their soldiers to fight the other 5 tribes, and the 4 tribes from the east won. So Kedorlayomer became the boss over the other 5 tribes too.  
\p Those 5 tribes let him be their boss for 12 years. Then the next year, their leaders told Kedorlayomer that they didn’t want him to be their boss any more. Kedorlayomer got really angry, and the next year, he got soldiers from the 4 tribes in the east, and they went to fight those 5 tribes.  
\p On the way to that fight, Kedorlayomer’s soldiers had other fights with some other tribes, and they won all those fights. They beat the Refa tribe at \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place called Ashteroth-Karnayim, and they beat the Zuz tribe at \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place called Ham, and they beat the Em tribe at \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place called Shaveh-Kiriathayim, and they beat the Hor tribe in the hill country called Edom. They chased the Hor soldiers all the way to \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place called El-Paran, near the desert. Then Kedorlayomer and the soldiers from the east, they all went back to \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place called En-Mishpat. Another name for that place is Kadesh. Then Kedorlayomer and his mob fought the Amalek tribe and beat them, and took control of their country. Then they fought the Amor tribe in Hazazon-Tamar country, and beat them too.  
\p While Kedorlayomer and his mob were fighting those other people, the 5 tribes that didn’t want Kedorlayomer to be their boss, they went to the valley called Sidim. (Today there is salt water in that valley, and \w we|strong="H3068"\w* call it the \em Dead Sea\em*.) The soldiers of those 5 tribes got ready there to fight against Kedorlayomer and his 4 tribes from the east.  
\p So when Kedorlayomer and his mob got to that Sidim valley there was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big fight.  
\v 10 Kedorlayomer \w and|strong="H4428"\w* \w his|strong="H4428"\w* mob won \w that|strong="H4428"\w* fight. \w They|strong="H8033"\w* \w beat|strong="H4428"\w* those 5 tribes, \w and|strong="H4428"\w* \w their|strong="H5307"\w* soldiers all \w ran|strong="H5127"\w* \w away|strong="H5127"\w*. \w In|strong="H4428"\w* \w that|strong="H4428"\w* \w flat|strong="H5307"\w* \w country|strong="H2022"\w* \w there|strong="H8033"\w* \w were|strong="H2022"\w* lots \w of|strong="H4428"\w* holes \w in|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H8033"\w* ground \w that|strong="H4428"\w* \w were|strong="H2022"\w* full \w of|strong="H4428"\w* sticky black stuff, \w called|strong="H8033"\w* \em tar\em*. \w So|strong="H8033"\w* \w when|strong="H5127"\w* \w the|strong="H8033"\w* soldiers \w from|strong="H5127"\w* \w the|strong="H8033"\w* 5 tribes \w ran|strong="H5127"\w* \w away|strong="H5127"\w*, \w some|strong="H8033"\w* \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w them|strong="H5307"\w* \w fell|strong="H5307"\w* \w into|strong="H5307"\w* those holes. \w But|strong="H5127"\w* \w the|strong="H8033"\w* \w rest|strong="H7604"\w* \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w them|strong="H5307"\w* \w ran|strong="H5127"\w* \w up|strong="H4428"\w* \w into|strong="H5307"\w* \w the|strong="H8033"\w* \w hills|strong="H2022"\w*.   
\p
\v 11 \w So|strong="H3947"\w* Kedorlayomer \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w his|strong="H3605"\w* soldiers \w went|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w Sodom|strong="H5467"\w* \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w Gomorrah|strong="H6017"\w*, \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w they|strong="H3605"\w* grabbed \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* people \w that|strong="H3605"\w* lived \w there|strong="H3605"\w*. \w And|strong="H3212"\w* \w they|strong="H3605"\w* \w took|strong="H3947"\w* \w everything|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* people owned, even \w their|strong="H3605"\w* food, \w and|strong="H3212"\w* \w then|strong="H3947"\w* \w they|strong="H3605"\w* started \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w go|strong="H3212"\w* \w back|strong="H3947"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* own country.  
\v 12 \w At|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H1931"\w* time, Abram’s \w nephew|strong="H1121"\w* \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w* \w lived|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w Sodom|strong="H5467"\w*, \w so|strong="H3947"\w* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H1121"\w* grabbed \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w* too, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H3947"\w* family, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w all|strong="H3212"\w* \w their|strong="H3947"\w* things. \w Those|strong="H1121"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H1121"\w* \w took|strong="H3947"\w* \w all|strong="H3212"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w*’s mob \w away|strong="H3947"\w* \w with|strong="H3427"\w* \w them|strong="H3947"\w*.   
\s1 Abram saved Lot and his family  
\p
\v 13-14 \w A|strong="H3068"\w* man got away from Kedorlayomer and his mob, and he went and told Abram that they got Lot. At that time, Abram was living near the big trees that belonged to \w a|strong="H3068"\w* man called Mamreh. Abram was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* good friend of Mamreh, and also of Mamreh’s 2 brothers. Their names were Eskol and Aner. Mamreh and his brothers belonged to the Amor tribe, and Abram belonged to the Hebrew tribe, but they all looked after each other. \fig A man told Abram that Kedorlayomer’s mob got Lot|src="bible abraham informed about lot Gen 14.tif" size="col" ref="14:13-14" \fig*  
\p Abram had 318 men that knew how to fight. They worked for Abram all their lives, and Abram really trusted them. So Abram got those men, and Mamreh, Eskol and Aner got their fighting men, and they all went to fight Kedorlayomer and his soldiers. They followed them, and they found them at \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place to the north, called Dan.  
\v 15 \w Then|strong="H5650"\w*, \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w night|strong="H3915"\w* \w time|strong="H5704"\w*, \w Abram|strong="H2505"\w* split \w up|strong="H5921"\w* \w all|strong="H5704"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* fighting \w men|strong="H5650"\w* \w into|strong="H5921"\w* groups, \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w attacked|strong="H5221"\w* Kedorlayomer \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* \w soldiers|strong="H5650"\w*. \w Abram|strong="H2505"\w* \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w his|strong="H5921"\w* \w men|strong="H5650"\w* won \w that|strong="H1931"\w* fight, \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* \w chased|strong="H7291"\w* \w those|strong="H5921"\w* other \w soldiers|strong="H5650"\w* \w all|strong="H5704"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w way|strong="H5704"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town called \w Hobah|strong="H2327"\w*, \w north|strong="H8040"\w* \w of|strong="H5650"\w* \w Damascus|strong="H1834"\w* town.  
\v 16 \w That|strong="H5971"\w*’s how \w Abram|strong="H7725"\w*’s mob saved \w Lot|strong="H3876"\w*, \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* women, \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w from|strong="H7725"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* towns called Sodom \w and|strong="H7725"\w* Gomorrah, \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w they|strong="H5971"\w* got \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w their|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w too|strong="H1571"\w*. \w Then|strong="H1571"\w* \w they|strong="H5971"\w* \w all|strong="H3605"\w* started \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w go|strong="H7725"\w* \w back|strong="H7725"\w* south.   
\s1 Abram met Melkizedek  
\p
\v 17 \w After|strong="H3318"\w* \w Abram|strong="H7725"\w*’s mob \w beat|strong="H5221"\w* Kedorlayomer \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w his|strong="H7725"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w while|strong="H1931"\w* \w they|strong="H1931"\w* \w were|strong="H4428"\w* \w going|strong="H3318"\w* \w back|strong="H7725"\w* south \w on|strong="H3318"\w* \w their|strong="H7725"\w* \w way|strong="H7125"\w* \w home|strong="H7725"\w*, \w the|strong="H5221"\w* leader \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w Sodom|strong="H5467"\w* \w went|strong="H3318"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w meet|strong="H7125"\w* \w Abram|strong="H7725"\w* \w in|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H5221"\w* \w valley|strong="H6010"\w* called \em Shaveh\em*. Another name \w for|strong="H4428"\w* \w that|strong="H1931"\w* place \w is|strong="H1931"\w* \em the valley that belongs to the leader\em*.   
\p
\v 18 There \w was|strong="H1931"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town \w in|strong="H4428"\w* \w that|strong="H1931"\w* country called \w Salem|strong="H8004"\w*, \w and|strong="H4428"\w* \w the|strong="H3318"\w* boss \w over|strong="H4428"\w* \w that|strong="H1931"\w* town \w was|strong="H1931"\w* called Melkizedek. \w He|strong="H1931"\w* \w was|strong="H1931"\w* \w also|strong="H4428"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* leader \w of|strong="H4428"\w* God’s ceremonies. \w He|strong="H1931"\w* worked \w for|strong="H4428"\w* God, \w the|strong="H3318"\w* \w one|strong="H1931"\w* \w that|strong="H1931"\w* \w is|strong="H1931"\w* more powerful \w than|strong="H4428"\w* \w any|strong="H3318"\w* other god. Well, Melkizedek \w also|strong="H4428"\w* \w went|strong="H3318"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w meet|strong="H3318"\w* Abram \w and|strong="H4428"\w* \w his|strong="H3318"\w* men, \w and|strong="H4428"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w gave|strong="H3318"\w* \w them|strong="H3318"\w* some \w bread|strong="H3899"\w* \w and|strong="H4428"\w* some \w wine|strong="H3196"\w*.  
\v 19 \w Then|strong="H5945"\w* Melkizedek prayed \w for|strong="H8064"\w* Abram. \w He|strong="H1288"\w* said,  
\q1 “\w God|strong="H8064"\w*, \w you|strong="H1288"\w* \w are|strong="H8064"\w* more powerful than \w any|strong="H7069"\w* other \w god|strong="H8064"\w*.  
\q1 \w You|strong="H1288"\w* \w are|strong="H8064"\w* \w the|strong="H1288"\w* one \w that|strong="H1288"\w* \w made|strong="H1288"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8064"\w* \w and|strong="H8064"\w* \w earth|strong="H8064"\w*.  
\q1 \w I|strong="H1288"\w*’m asking \w you|strong="H1288"\w* \w to|strong="H8064"\w* \w be|strong="H1288"\w* really good \w to|strong="H8064"\w* Abram.   
\q1
\v 20 \w I|strong="H5414"\w* want \w everyone|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H5414"\w* say \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w are|strong="H3027"\w* great, \w and|strong="H3027"\w* more powerful \w than|strong="H3605"\w* \w any|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H3605"\w* \w god|strong="H5414"\w*.  
\q1 \w You|strong="H5414"\w* \w are|strong="H3027"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w one|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w helped|strong="H3027"\w* Abram fight \w with|strong="H3027"\w* \w his|strong="H3605"\w* \w enemies|strong="H6862"\w* \w and|strong="H3027"\w* win.”  
\m \w Then|strong="H5414"\w* Abram got \w all|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* got \w after|strong="H4643"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* fight, \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w used|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H5414"\w* belong \w to|strong="H5414"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* Sodom \w and|strong="H3027"\w* Gomorrah mob, \w and|strong="H3027"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* split \w those|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w up|strong="H5414"\w* \w into|strong="H3027"\w* 10 groups. \w And|strong="H3027"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* \w one|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H3027"\w* \w those|strong="H3605"\w* groups \w of|strong="H3027"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H5414"\w* Melkizedek.\x * \xo 14:20 \xt Hebrews 7:1-10\x*   
\p
\v 21 \w Then|strong="H3947"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* leader \w of|strong="H4428"\w* \w Sodom|strong="H5467"\w* said \w to|strong="H5414"\w* Abram, “\w I|strong="H5414"\w* only \w want|strong="H5315"\w* \w my|strong="H5414"\w* \w people|strong="H5315"\w* \w back|strong="H3947"\w*. \w You|strong="H5414"\w* \w can|strong="H3947"\w* \w keep|strong="H3947"\w* \w those|strong="H5315"\w* other things.”   
\p
\v 22 \w But|strong="H4428"\w* Abram said, “\w I|strong="H3068"\w* \w made|strong="H7311"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* strong \w promise|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w my|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*. \w His|strong="H3068"\w* name \w is|strong="H3068"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*. \w He|strong="H3068"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* more powerful \w than|strong="H4428"\w* \w any|strong="H7069"\w* other \w god|strong="H3068"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H3068"\w* \w made|strong="H7311"\w* \w heaven|strong="H8064"\w* \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w earth|strong="H8064"\w*.  
\v 23 \w I|strong="H5704"\w* promised \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w I|strong="H5704"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w take|strong="H3947"\w* \w anything|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* belongs \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w*. \w I|strong="H5704"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w even|strong="H5704"\w* \w take|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* bit \w of|strong="H3605"\w* string, \w or|strong="H3808"\w* \w anything|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* belongs \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w*. \w You|strong="H3605"\w* see, \w I|strong="H5704"\w* don’t \w want|strong="H3808"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w tell|strong="H3605"\w* \w everyone|strong="H3605"\w* \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H3605"\w* \w gave|strong="H3947"\w* \w me|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lot \w of|strong="H3605"\w* \w things|strong="H3605"\w* \w and|strong="H3947"\w* \w made|strong="H6238"\w* \w me|strong="H3947"\w* \w rich|strong="H6238"\w*.  
\v 24 \w No|strong="H3947"\w*. \w The|strong="H3947"\w* \w only|strong="H7535"\w* thing \w that|strong="H5288"\w* \w I|strong="H5288"\w* \w will|strong="H5288"\w* \w keep|strong="H3947"\w* \w is|strong="H5288"\w* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* food \w that|strong="H5288"\w* \w I|strong="H5288"\w* ate \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* food \w that|strong="H5288"\w* \w my|strong="H3947"\w* fighting \w men|strong="H5288"\w* ate. \w And|strong="H1980"\w* \w these|strong="H1992"\w* \w men|strong="H5288"\w*, Mamreh, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w Aner|strong="H6063"\w*, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* Eskol, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w their|strong="H3947"\w* fighting \w men|strong="H5288"\w*, \w they|strong="H1992"\w* helped \w me|strong="H3947"\w* \w save|strong="H1107"\w* \w your|strong="H3947"\w* \w people|strong="H5288"\w* \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w your|strong="H3947"\w* \w things|strong="H1992"\w* too, \w so|strong="H1980"\w* \w you|strong="H3947"\w* \w can|strong="H3947"\w* \w give|strong="H3947"\w* \w them|strong="H1992"\w* \w some|strong="H1992"\w* \w of|strong="H2506"\w* \w those|strong="H1992"\w* \w things|strong="H1992"\w*.”   
\c 15  
\s1 God promised to give Abram a son  
\p
\v 1 \w Later|strong="H1961"\w* \w on|strong="H3068"\w*, \w after|strong="H1961"\w* Abram saved Lot, Abram \w had|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* dream, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* talked \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w him|strong="H7235"\w* \w in|strong="H3068"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* dream. \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1697"\w*, “Abram, don’t \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w frightened|strong="H3372"\w*, \w I|strong="H1697"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* always \w keep|strong="H1961"\w* \w you|strong="H3372"\w* safe, \w so|strong="H1961"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* nobody can ever \w hurt|strong="H1697"\w* \w you|strong="H3372"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w I|strong="H1697"\w* \w am|strong="H1961"\w* going \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w give|strong="H7235"\w* \w you|strong="H3372"\w* lots \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w good|strong="H3966"\w* \w things|strong="H1697"\w*.”   
\p
\v 2-3 Then Abram talked to God, and he called God by his special name \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*. He said, “\w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, you are very powerful. But look, I’ve got no son, so it doesn’t matter what you give me. You haven’t given me the one thing I really want. You haven’t given me any kids. So when I die, one of my work-men will get all my things. His name is Eliyezer. He is from Damascus.”   
\p
\v 4 \w Then|strong="H3318"\w* Abram \w heard|strong="H3588"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w talk|strong="H1697"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w him|strong="H3318"\w* again. \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H1697"\w*, “\w I|strong="H3588"\w* tell \w you|strong="H3588"\w*, \w that|strong="H3588"\w* work-man \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w get|strong="H3318"\w* \w all|strong="H1697"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w things|strong="H1697"\w* \w after|strong="H3588"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* die. \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w going|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* give \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* son, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w get|strong="H3318"\w* \w all|strong="H1697"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w things|strong="H1697"\w* \w after|strong="H3588"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* die.”   
\p
\v 5 \w Then|strong="H1961"\w* \w God|strong="H8064"\w* \w took|strong="H3318"\w* Abram \w outside|strong="H2351"\w* \w and|strong="H8064"\w* \w said|strong="H3318"\w*, “\w Look|strong="H5027"\w* \w up|strong="H3318"\w* \w at|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3541"\w* \w sky|strong="H8064"\w* \w and|strong="H8064"\w* try \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w count|strong="H5608"\w* \w all|strong="H3201"\w* \w those|strong="H3318"\w* \w stars|strong="H3556"\w*. \w There|strong="H1961"\w* \w are|strong="H8064"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lot \w of|strong="H2233"\w* \w stars|strong="H3556"\w*. \w You|strong="H2233"\w* \w can|strong="H3201"\w*’t \w count|strong="H5608"\w* \w them|strong="H3318"\w* \w all|strong="H3201"\w*. Well, \w you|strong="H2233"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w have|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H2233"\w*, \w and|strong="H8064"\w* \w later|strong="H1961"\w* \w on|strong="H1961"\w* lots \w of|strong="H2233"\w* people \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w born|strong="H3318"\w* \w into|strong="H3318"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* \w family|strong="H2233"\w*, \w and|strong="H8064"\w* \w later|strong="H1961"\w* \w on|strong="H1961"\w* \w they|strong="H3541"\w* \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* real big \w family|strong="H2233"\w*. \w And|strong="H8064"\w* just \w like|strong="H1961"\w* nobody \w can|strong="H3201"\w* \w count|strong="H5608"\w* \w the|strong="H3541"\w* \w stars|strong="H3556"\w*, nobody \w will|strong="H1961"\w* \w be|strong="H1961"\w* \w able|strong="H3201"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w count|strong="H5608"\w* \w all|strong="H3201"\w* \w your|strong="H1961"\w* \w family|strong="H2233"\w*.”\x * \xo 15:5 \xt Romans 4:18; Hebrews 11:12\x* \fig God promised Abram a really big family, he promised him lots of people, just like there are lots of stars|src="lll1-16.tif" size="col" ref="15:5" \fig*   
\p
\v 6 \w And|strong="H3068"\w* Abram believed what \w God|strong="H3068"\w* said, so \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w was|strong="H3068"\w* really happy \w with|strong="H3068"\w* \w him|strong="H2803"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* told \w him|strong="H2803"\w*, “You believe \w me|strong="H2803"\w*, so now \w I|strong="H3068"\w*’m saying you \w are|strong="H3068"\w* \w properly|strong="H6666"\w* good, \w like|strong="H2803"\w* you never \w did|strong="H3068"\w* anything wrong.”\x * \xo 15:6 \xt Romans 4:3, 9, 22; Galatians 3:6; Hebrews 11:11; James 2:23\x*   
\s1 God did a ceremony to make Abram sure about his promises  
\p
\v 7 \w Then|strong="H3318"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w* \w said|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* Abram, “\w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w God|strong="H3068"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w my|strong="H5414"\w* name \w is|strong="H3068"\w* \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*. \w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* \w one|strong="H3068"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w brought|strong="H3318"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w out|strong="H3318"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* \w your|strong="H3068"\w* \w home|strong="H3068"\w* country, \w from|strong="H3318"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* town called Ur, \w in|strong="H3068"\w* Chaldia country. \w And|strong="H3068"\w* \w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w going|strong="H3318"\w* \w to|strong="H3318"\w* \w give|strong="H5414"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w this|strong="H2063"\w* country \w here|strong="H2063"\w*. \w It|strong="H5414"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w be|strong="H3068"\w* \w yours|strong="H5414"\w*. \w You|strong="H5414"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* own \w all|strong="H5414"\w* \w this|strong="H2063"\w* country.”   
\p
\v 8 Abram said \w to|strong="H3045"\w* \w God|strong="H3069"\w*, “\w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w*, \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w know|strong="H3045"\w* \w you|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H4100"\w* \w very|strong="H3045"\w* powerful, \w but|strong="H3588"\w* \w how|strong="H4100"\w* \w can|strong="H4100"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w be|strong="H3069"\w* really \w sure|strong="H3045"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H4100"\w* get \w all|strong="H3045"\w* \w this|strong="H3588"\w* country?”   
\p
\v 9 \w So|strong="H3947"\w* God said \w to|strong="H3947"\w* Abram, “\w Bring|strong="H3947"\w* \w me|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w cow|strong="H5697"\w* \w that|strong="H3947"\w* hasn’t had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* baby, \w and|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w female|strong="H5795"\w* \w goat|strong="H5795"\w*, \w and|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* male sheep. \w All|strong="H3947"\w* those animals \w have|strong="H3947"\w* \w to|strong="H3947"\w* be 3 years \w old|strong="H8027"\w*. \w And|strong="H3947"\w* I want \w you|strong="H3947"\w* \w to|strong="H3947"\w* \w bring|strong="H3947"\w* \w me|strong="H3947"\w* 2 different sorts \w of|strong="H3947"\w* pigeons too.”   
\p
\v 10 \w Then|strong="H3947"\w* Abram \w did|strong="H3808"\w* what \w God|strong="H5414"\w* told \w him|strong="H5414"\w*. \w He|strong="H3605"\w* killed \w those|strong="H3605"\w* animals \w and|strong="H3947"\w* \w birds|strong="H6833"\w*, \w and|strong="H3947"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* \w cut|strong="H1334"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* animals \w in|strong="H8432"\w* \w half|strong="H1335"\w*. \w He|strong="H3605"\w* \w put|strong="H5414"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* halves \w of|strong="H8432"\w* \w each|strong="H3605"\w* animal \w on|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* ground \w in|strong="H8432"\w* 2 lines facing \w each|strong="H3605"\w* \w other|strong="H7453"\w*. \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w he|strong="H3605"\w* didn’t \w cut|strong="H1334"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w birds|strong="H6833"\w* \w in|strong="H8432"\w* \w half|strong="H1335"\w*.  
\v 11 \w Then|strong="H3381"\w* some hawks flew \w down|strong="H3381"\w* \w and|strong="H3381"\w* tried \w to|strong="H3381"\w* eat \w the|strong="H5921"\w* animals, \w but|strong="H5921"\w* Abram chased \w them|strong="H5921"\w* \w away|strong="H5380"\w*.   
\p
\v 12 \w While|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w sun|strong="H8121"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w going|strong="H5307"\w* \w down|strong="H5307"\w*, Abram \w went|strong="H8121"\w* \w to|strong="H1961"\w* \w sleep|strong="H8639"\w*. \w It|strong="H5921"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w strong|strong="H1419"\w* \w deep|strong="H8639"\w* \w sleep|strong="H8639"\w*. \w Then|strong="H1961"\w* Abram \w had|strong="H1961"\w* something \w like|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* dream. \w It|strong="H5921"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* really dark \w for|strong="H5921"\w* \w him|strong="H5921"\w*, \w and|strong="H1419"\w* \w he|strong="H5921"\w* felt really frightened.\x * \xo 15:12 \xt Job 4:13-14\x*  
\v 13-15 God said to Abram, “I want you to know for sure what will happen after you get really old. You don’t have to worry about anything. You see, you will live to be \w a|strong="H3068"\w* very old man, and then, when you are dying, you will feel good inside, and your family will bury you right here, in this country. But I have to tell you something. After you die, your family will leave this country and move to another country that belongs to other people. Your family will live in that country, and later on, the other people in that country will make your family like prisoners, and your family will have to work very hard for them. Those people will do really bad things to your family for 400 years. After that, I will save your family from that hard time, and I will punish those people for doing bad things to your family. Then your family will leave that country, and they will take \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lot of animals and things with them. They will be really rich.\x * \xo 15:13-15 \xt Exodus 1:1-14; Acts 7:6\x*  
\v 16 \w And|strong="H7725"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w bring|strong="H7725"\w* \w your|strong="H7725"\w* family \w back|strong="H7725"\w* \w here|strong="H2008"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w this|strong="H3588"\w* country. \w You|strong="H3588"\w* see, \w the|strong="H3588"\w* Amor tribe \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H5771"\w* \w here|strong="H2008"\w* \w in|strong="H7725"\w* \w this|strong="H3588"\w* country \w now|strong="H2008"\w*, \w they|strong="H3588"\w* do \w really|strong="H7725"\w* bad \w things|strong="H3808"\w*, \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* \w are|strong="H5771"\w* getting worse \w and|strong="H7725"\w* worse. \w But|strong="H3588"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* punish \w them|strong="H7725"\w* \w yet|strong="H3588"\w*. \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* punish \w them|strong="H7725"\w* later, \w after|strong="H3588"\w* \w your|strong="H7725"\w* grand-kids grow \w up|strong="H5704"\w* \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w have|strong="H5771"\w* grand-kids. \w Then|strong="H7725"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* do payback \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* mob \w in|strong="H7725"\w* \w this|strong="H3588"\w* country \w for|strong="H3588"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* bad \w things|strong="H3808"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w they|strong="H3588"\w* do. \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w take|strong="H7725"\w* \w their|strong="H7725"\w* country \w from|strong="H7725"\w* \w them|strong="H7725"\w*, \w and|strong="H7725"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w will|strong="H3808"\w* \w give|strong="H7725"\w* \w it|strong="H3588"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w your|strong="H7725"\w* family.” \w That|strong="H3588"\w*’s \w what|strong="H2008"\w* \w God|strong="H3808"\w* told \w Abram|strong="H7725"\w*.   
\p
\v 17 \w After|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H5674"\w* \w sun|strong="H8121"\w* \w went|strong="H5674"\w* down \w and|strong="H5674"\w* \w it|strong="H1961"\w* \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w dark|strong="H5939"\w*, Abram \w saw|strong="H2009"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* bucket \w full|strong="H5674"\w* \w of|strong="H8121"\w* fire, \w with|strong="H5674"\w* \w smoke|strong="H6227"\w* \w coming|strong="H2009"\w* \w out|strong="H5674"\w* \w of|strong="H8121"\w* \w it|strong="H1961"\w*, \w and|strong="H5674"\w* \w he|strong="H8121"\w* \w saw|strong="H2009"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w burning|strong="H3940"\w* stick \w with|strong="H5674"\w* \w it|strong="H1961"\w*. \w That|strong="H1961"\w* bucket \w and|strong="H5674"\w* stick moved \w along|strong="H5674"\w* \w between|strong="H5674"\w* \w the|strong="H5674"\w* halves \w of|strong="H8121"\w* \w those|strong="H1961"\w* \w animals|strong="H1961"\w* \w that|strong="H1961"\w* Abram killed.\fig God made a bucket of fire and a burning stick move between the animals, to show Abram that he was going to do everything he promised|src="01_Gen 15_Covenant_R.tif" size="col" ref="15:17" \fig*  
\v 18-21 That’s how God showed Abram that he was really going to do everything that he promised. God said, “I am going to give all this country to the people that will be born into your family. From the river in Egypt in the south, right up to the big river called Euphrates in the north.  
\p These are the tribes in this country now,  
\li1 – the Ken tribe,  
\li1 – the Keniz tribe,  
\li1 – the Kadmon tribe,  
\li1 – the Heth tribe,  
\li1 – the Periz tribe,  
\li1 – the Refa tribe,  
\li1 – the Amor tribe,  
\li1 – the Canaan tribe,  
\li1 – the Girgash tribe,  
\li1 – the Jebus tribe.  
\m I will take this country away from all those tribes, and I will give it to your family.” God promised that to Abram.\x * \xo 15:18-21 \xt Acts 7:5\x*   
\c 16  
\s1 The story about Hagar and Ishmael  
\p
\v 1-3 Abram and Sarai lived in that Canaan country, and after they were there for 10 years, they still had no kids. Sarai had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* woman from Egypt working for her, called Hagar. She was Sarai’s slave. That means Sarai owned Hagar, and Hagar had to do everything that Sarai told her to do.  
\p Sarai was sad because she had no kids, but she got an idea about how to get \w a|strong="H3068"\w* baby for herself. So she said to Abram, “God has stopped me from having my own kids. But listen. I want you to sleep with Hagar, like she is your wife. You see, she belongs to me, so if she has \w a|strong="H3068"\w* baby, that baby will really belong to me.” So Abram did that, just like Sarai said.  
\v 4 \w He|strong="H3588"\w* slept \w with|strong="H5869"\w* \w Hagar|strong="H1904"\w* \w like|strong="H5869"\w* \w she|strong="H3588"\w* \w was|strong="H1404"\w* \w his|strong="H7200"\w* wife.  
\p \w Then|strong="H7200"\w* \w Hagar|strong="H1904"\w* found \w out|strong="H7200"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w she|strong="H3588"\w* \w was|strong="H1404"\w* going \w to|strong="H7200"\w* \w have|strong="H5869"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* baby, \w so|strong="H3588"\w* \w she|strong="H3588"\w* started rubbishing \w Sarai|strong="H1404"\w* \w all|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H7200"\w* time, \w because|strong="H3588"\w* \w Sarai|strong="H1404"\w* didn’t \w have|strong="H5869"\w* \w any|strong="H7200"\w* kids.  
\v 5 \w So|strong="H5414"\w* \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w* said \w to|strong="H3068"\w* Abram, “\w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w blame|strong="H5414"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w for|strong="H3588"\w* \w this|strong="H5414"\w* trouble. \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* Hagar \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w now|strong="H3588"\w* \w she|strong="H3588"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* going \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* baby, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w she|strong="H3588"\w* \w is|strong="H3068"\w* rubbishing \w me|strong="H5414"\w* \w all|strong="H7200"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w time|strong="H5921"\w*. \w I|strong="H3588"\w* reckon \w God|strong="H3068"\w* knows \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w I|strong="H3588"\w* \w am|strong="H3068"\w* \w right|strong="H3068"\w*, \w and|strong="H3068"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w are|strong="H5869"\w* \w wrong|strong="H2555"\w*.”   
\p
\v 6 \w But|strong="H2009"\w* Abram said \w to|strong="H6213"\w* \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w*, “Hagar belongs \w to|strong="H6213"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w*. \w You|strong="H6440"\w* \w are|strong="H5869"\w* \w her|strong="H6031"\w* boss, \w so|strong="H6213"\w* \w do|strong="H6213"\w* \w whatever|strong="H2896"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* want \w with|strong="H6213"\w* \w her|strong="H6031"\w*.” \w Then|strong="H2009"\w* \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w* started \w to|strong="H6213"\w* \w treat|strong="H6213"\w* Hagar \w in|strong="H6213"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* really bad \w way|strong="H6440"\w*. \w So|strong="H6213"\w* Hagar \w left|strong="H1272"\w* Abram \w and|strong="H3027"\w* \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w*’s camp \w and|strong="H3027"\w* \w ran|strong="H1272"\w* \w away|strong="H1272"\w*.   
\p
\v 7 Hagar started walking \w through|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w desert|strong="H4057"\w*, \w along|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w road|strong="H1870"\w* \w that|strong="H3068"\w* \w went|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town called \w Shur|strong="H7793"\w*, \w near|strong="H5921"\w* Egypt. \w She|strong="H5921"\w* sat \w down|strong="H1870"\w* \w next|strong="H5921"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* water-hole \w there|strong="H4672"\w* \w in|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w desert|strong="H4057"\w*. \w God|strong="H3068"\w*’s \w angel|strong="H4397"\w* \w messenger|strong="H4397"\w* \w went|strong="H3068"\w* \w to|strong="H3068"\w* \w her|strong="H5921"\w* \w there|strong="H4672"\w*.  
\v 8 \w He|strong="H6440"\w* said, “\w Hagar|strong="H1904"\w*, \w you|strong="H6440"\w* belong \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w*, \w so|strong="H2088"\w* why \w are|strong="H6440"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* sitting \w out|strong="H6440"\w* \w here|strong="H2088"\w* \w in|strong="H3212"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* desert? \w Where|strong="H2088"\w* \w are|strong="H6440"\w* \w you|strong="H6440"\w* \w going|strong="H3212"\w*?”  
\p \w Hagar|strong="H1904"\w* said, “\w I|strong="H2088"\w*’m running \w away|strong="H3212"\w* \w from|strong="H6440"\w* \w my|strong="H6440"\w* boss \w Sarai|strong="H8297"\w*. \w She|strong="H6440"\w* \w is|strong="H2088"\w* too hard \w on|strong="H3212"\w* \w me|strong="H6440"\w*.”   
\p
