\v 16 \w Then|strong="H2009"\w* Abimelek said \w to|strong="H5414"\w* \w Sarah|strong="H8283"\w*, “\w I|strong="H5414"\w*’m \w giving|strong="H5414"\w* Abraham, \w your|strong="H3605"\w* brother, \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lot \w of|strong="H5869"\w* \w money|strong="H3701"\w*, \w to|strong="H5414"\w* \w pay|strong="H5414"\w* \w for|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* trouble \w I|strong="H5414"\w* \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w*. \w I|strong="H5414"\w*’m \w giving|strong="H5414"\w* \w him|strong="H5414"\w* 1,000 pieces \w of|strong="H5869"\w* \w silver|strong="H3701"\w* \w money|strong="H3701"\w* \w to|strong="H5414"\w* \w show|strong="H5414"\w* \w your|strong="H3605"\w* mob, \w and|strong="H3701"\w* \w everyone|strong="H3605"\w* \w else|strong="H3605"\w*, \w that|strong="H3605"\w* \w you|strong="H5414"\w* \w did|strong="H5869"\w* \w nothing|strong="H3605"\w* wrong.”   
\p
\v 17-18 Then Abraham prayed to God and asked him to make Abimelek and his mob better. You see, before, at the time when Abimelek got Sarah so that he could marry her, God made Abimelek sick and stopped all the women in Abimelek’s house from having babies. But then God talked to Abimelek, and Abimelek gave Sarah back to Abraham. So then Abraham prayed to God, and God made Abimelek better, and he made Abimelek’s wife better, and he made all the women that lived in Abimelek’s house better too, so that they had babies again.   
\c 21  
