\v 20-21 God kept Ishmael safe as he grew up in the desert called Paran. He learned how to use \w a|strong="H3068"\w* bow and arrows properly, so he became \w a|strong="H3068"\w* good hunter. And later on, Hagar got \w a|strong="H3068"\w* wife for him from Egypt country.   
\s1 Abraham and Abimelek made strong promises to each other  
\p
\v 22-23 One day, Abimelek went to talk to Abraham. Abimelek was the big boss of the country where Abraham lived. And Ficol, the leader of Abimelek’s army, went with him. Abimelek said to Abraham, “You know, you are not one of my people. You came from another place to live here in my country. But I have been good to you, and to all your people. So I want you to promise me that you will never try to trick me, or my kids, or anyone that is born into my family. I want you to promise that you will be good to them. We know that God is very good to you, and he helps you with everything you do. So I want you to make that promise to me while God is listening. I want you to tell God to punish you if you break that promise.”\x * \xo 21:22-23 \xt Genesis 26:26\x*   
\p
\v 24 \w So|strong="H7650"\w* Abraham \w made|strong="H7650"\w* that \w promise|strong="H7650"\w* \w to|strong="H7650"\w* Abimelek. \w He|strong="H7650"\w* said those words \w in|strong="H7650"\w* \w the|strong="H7650"\w* way that Abimelek wanted.   
\p
\v 25 \w But|strong="H3198"\w* \w then|strong="H5650"\w* Abraham also \w complained|strong="H3198"\w* \w to|strong="H5921"\w* Abimelek. \w He|strong="H5921"\w* said, “\w I|strong="H5921"\w*’ve got \w a|strong="H3068"\w* problem. Some \w of|strong="H5650"\w* \w your|strong="H5921"\w* workers \w took|strong="H1497"\w* one \w of|strong="H5650"\w* \w my|strong="H5921"\w* water-holes, \w and|strong="H5650"\w* \w then|strong="H5650"\w* \w they|strong="H5921"\w* stopped \w my|strong="H5921"\w* workers \w from|strong="H5921"\w* getting any \w water|strong="H4325"\w* there.”   
\p
\v 26 Abimelek \w said|strong="H1697"\w*, “\w I|strong="H3117"\w*’m sorry, Abraham. \w I|strong="H3117"\w* don’t \w know|strong="H3045"\w* \w who|strong="H4310"\w* \w did|strong="H6213"\w* \w that|strong="H3045"\w*. \w I|strong="H3117"\w* \w never|strong="H3808"\w* \w heard|strong="H8085"\w* \w about|strong="H1697"\w* \w it|strong="H6213"\w*, \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w you|strong="H3117"\w* didn’t \w tell|strong="H5046"\w* \w me|strong="H5046"\w* \w about|strong="H1697"\w* \w it|strong="H6213"\w* \w until|strong="H1115"\w* \w now|strong="H3117"\w*.”   
\p
