\p
\v 62 Abraham’s son \w Isaac|strong="H3327"\w* \w was|strong="H1931"\w* \w living|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* Canaan \w country|strong="H5045"\w*. \w You|strong="H3427"\w* see, \w before|strong="H3427"\w* \w this|strong="H1931"\w* time, \w Isaac|strong="H3327"\w* \w went|strong="H3327"\w* \w south|strong="H5045"\w*, away \w from|strong="H3427"\w* Abraham’s camp, \w and|strong="H3427"\w* \w he|strong="H1931"\w* made \w his|strong="H3327"\w* camp \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H3427"\w* \w south|strong="H5045"\w* \w part|strong="H1931"\w* \w of|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H3427"\w* \w country|strong="H5045"\w* called \w the|strong="H3427"\w* \w Negev|strong="H5045"\w*, near \w a|strong="H3068"\w* water-hole. \w That|strong="H1931"\w* water-hole \w was|strong="H1931"\w* called \em the water-hole that belongs to God, he is alive and sees me\em*. Then \w when|strong="H3427"\w* Abraham’s worker \w was|strong="H1931"\w* away \w in|strong="H3427"\w* Haran, \w Isaac|strong="H3327"\w* came back home.   
