\p
\v 7-8 Abraham lived \w a|strong="H3068"\w* long time, until he was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* very old man. He lived until he was 175 years old. He had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* good long life, then he breathed for the last time, and he died.   
\p
\v 9-10 Then Abraham’s 2 oldest sons, Isaac and Ishmael, they took Abraham’s body to the cave at the place called Makpelah, to the east of the place called Mamreh. You see, \w a|strong="H3068"\w* long time before that, Abraham bought that cave and the land around it from \w a|strong="H3068"\w* man called Efron. Efron’s father was called Zohar, and they were from the Heth tribe. And Abraham put his wife Sarah’s body in that cave. So after Abraham died, Isaac and Ishmael put his body in that cave, next to Sarah’s body.\x * \xo 25:9-10 \xt Genesis 23:3-16\x*   
\p
