\v 20-22 Jacob prayed to God. He said, “God, you know that I’m walking \w a|strong="H3068"\w* long way to Haran. Please stay with me and look after me while I’m away. Please give me food to eat and clothes to wear. And please keep me safe, so that one day I can go back home to my family.”  
\p Then Jacob made promises to God. He said, “God, if you will do all those things that I asked, then I will respect you properly, and you \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* will be my God. And this special stone that I put here, it will show people that you are here in this place, and people can come here to show you respect. And I promise that whenever you give me good things, I will always split them up into 10 parts and give one part back to you.”   
\c 29  
\s1 Jacob went to Haran  
\p
\v 1 \w Then|strong="H5375"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* left \w that|strong="H1121"\w* place, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w he|strong="H7272"\w* kept \w on|strong="H3212"\w* \w walking|strong="H3212"\w* towards \w the|strong="H5375"\w* \w east|strong="H6924"\w*, until \w he|strong="H7272"\w* got \w to|strong="H3212"\w* Paddan Aram \w country|strong="H6924"\w*.  
\v 2-3 Then Jacob looked at the land that was in front of him, and he saw \w a|strong="H3068"\w* water-hole with \w a|strong="H3068"\w* really big flat stone over the top, like \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lid. And he saw 3 mobs of sheep lying next to that water-hole. There were some work-men there that looked after those sheep. Every day, those work-men used to meet together at that water-hole with their sheep, and then they worked together to move that big stone that was on top of the water-hole, and they got water for their sheep to drink. Then every day they put that big stone on top of the water-hole again.   
\p
\v 4 \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w went|strong="H3290"\w* \w and|strong="H3290"\w* talked \w to|strong="H3290"\w* those work-men. \w He|strong="H3290"\w* said, “Hello. Where do you mob come \w from|strong="H3290"\w*?”  
\p \w The|strong="H3290"\w* work-men said, “We are \w from|strong="H3290"\w* \w Haran|strong="H2771"\w*.”   
\p
