\v 29-30 Jacob said to Laban, “Look, you know that I worked really hard for you. When I came here, you only had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* few animals. I looked after those animals for you, and they kept on having lots of babies, so now you have lots and lots of animals. Yes, \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* my God was good to you all the time that I worked for you. But I don’t have any animals myself. So now it’s time for me to look after myself and my own family.”   
\p
