\p
\v 49-50 Then Laban said to Jacob, “Tomorrow, you will go to your home country, and I will go back to my home country, and \w we|strong="H3068"\w* will not see each other any more. So I’m asking \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* your God to always watch both of us. If you treat my daughters badly, or if you marry any other women, remember that God will see you do those things. Even if nobody else sees you, God will see you.”  
\p So that place is also called \em Mizpah\em*. That name means \em place where he watches\em*.   
\p
\v 51 \w Then|strong="H2009"\w* \w Laban|strong="H3837"\w* said \w to|strong="H3290"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w*, “\w Look|strong="H2009"\w* \w at|strong="H3384"\w* \w this|strong="H2088"\w* \w pile|strong="H1530"\w* \w of|strong="H4676"\w* stones, \w and|strong="H3290"\w* \w this|strong="H2088"\w* \w other|strong="H2088"\w* big \w stone|strong="H1530"\w*. \w We|strong="H2009"\w* \w have|strong="H2009"\w* put \w them|strong="H3384"\w* \w here|strong="H2009"\w*, between \w my|strong="H3290"\w* country \w and|strong="H3290"\w* \w your|strong="H2088"\w* country.  
