\v 53 \w I|strong="H7650"\w*’m asking \w the|strong="H8199"\w* gods \w of|strong="H6343"\w* \w our|strong="H8199"\w* grand-fathers \w to|strong="H7650"\w* watch \w us|strong="H8199"\w* \w and|strong="H3290"\w* \w judge|strong="H8199"\w* \w us|strong="H8199"\w*. \w I|strong="H7650"\w*’m asking \w the|strong="H8199"\w* God \w of|strong="H6343"\w* \w your|strong="H8199"\w* grand-father Abraham, \w and|strong="H3290"\w* \w the|strong="H8199"\w* god \w of|strong="H6343"\w* \w my|strong="H3290"\w* grand-father \w Nahor|strong="H5152"\w* \w and|strong="H3290"\w* \w their|strong="H3290"\w* father Terah. Those gods \w will|strong="H3290"\w* keep \w on|strong="H7650"\w* watching \w us|strong="H8199"\w*, \w and|strong="H3290"\w* they \w will|strong="H3290"\w* know if one \w of|strong="H6343"\w* \w us|strong="H8199"\w* does \w the|strong="H8199"\w* wrong thing.”  
\p Then \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w made|strong="H7650"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* strong \w promise|strong="H7650"\w* \w to|strong="H7650"\w* Laban. \w He|strong="H3290"\w* said, “\w I|strong="H7650"\w* \w promise|strong="H7650"\w* \w that|strong="H8199"\w* \w I|strong="H7650"\w* \w will|strong="H3290"\w* not go past these stones \w into|strong="H8199"\w* \w your|strong="H8199"\w* country, \w to|strong="H7650"\w* hurt \w you|strong="H6343"\w*. \w I|strong="H7650"\w*’m making \w this|strong="H8199"\w* \w promise|strong="H7650"\w* \w with|strong="H8199"\w* God listening. \w He|strong="H3290"\w* \w is|strong="H3290"\w* \w the|strong="H8199"\w* one \w that|strong="H8199"\w* \w my|strong="H3290"\w* father \w Isaac|strong="H3327"\w* respected.”   
\p
\v 54 \w Then|strong="H7121"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w killed|strong="H2076"\w* \w an|strong="H7121"\w* animal \w and|strong="H3899"\w* burned \w it|strong="H7121"\w*, \w to|strong="H7121"\w* show respect \w to|strong="H7121"\w* God. \w He|strong="H7121"\w* \w did|strong="H2022"\w* \w that|strong="H7121"\w* right \w there|strong="H2022"\w*, \w in|strong="H3899"\w* \w the|strong="H7121"\w* \w hill|strong="H2022"\w* \w country|strong="H2022"\w*. \w Then|strong="H7121"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w said|strong="H7121"\w* \w to|strong="H7121"\w* \w his|strong="H7121"\w* relatives, “Come \w and|strong="H3899"\w* \w eat|strong="H3899"\w* \w food|strong="H3899"\w* \w with|strong="H3899"\w* \w me|strong="H7121"\w*.” \w So|strong="H7121"\w* \w they|strong="H7121"\w* \w all|strong="H3885"\w* ate \w food|strong="H3899"\w*, \w and|strong="H3899"\w* \w then|strong="H7121"\w* \w they|strong="H7121"\w* \w spent|strong="H3885"\w* \w the|strong="H7121"\w* \w night|strong="H3885"\w* \w in|strong="H3899"\w* \w that|strong="H7121"\w* place.   
\p
\v 55 Early the next morning, Laban got up. He kissed his grand-kids and his daughters, and he said \em goodbye\em* to them. Then Laban and his relatives left that place, and they went back to their home country.   
\c 32  
\s1 Angel messengers met with Jacob  
\p
\v 1 Jacob \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H7725"\w* \w relatives|strong="H1121"\w* \w left|strong="H7725"\w* \w that|strong="H1121"\w* \w place|strong="H4725"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w they|strong="H1242"\w* kept \w on|strong="H3212"\w* \w going|strong="H3212"\w* towards Jacob’s \w home|strong="H4725"\w* \w country|strong="H4725"\w*. \w On|strong="H3212"\w* \w the|strong="H7725"\w* \w way|strong="H3212"\w*, \w some|strong="H4725"\w* angel messengers \w from|strong="H7725"\w* God \w came|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H7725"\w* \w meet|strong="H1121"\w* Jacob.  
\v 2 \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w saw|strong="H3290"\w* \w those|strong="H1980"\w* \w angel|strong="H4397"\w* \w messengers|strong="H4397"\w*, \w and|strong="H1980"\w* \w he|strong="H1980"\w* said, “\w This|strong="H1870"\w* place \w is|strong="H1870"\w* God’s camp.” \w So|strong="H1980"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* called \w that|strong="H4397"\w* place \em Mahanayim\em*. \w That|strong="H4397"\w* name means \em 2 camps\em*.   
\s1 Jacob got frightened of Esau  
\p
