\v 16-17 Jacob and his family left Bethel, and they started going towards the town called Efrath. At that time, Jacob’s wife Rachel had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* baby growing inside her. And while they were still \w a|strong="H3068"\w* long way from Efrath, the time came for Rachel to have her baby. \w A|strong="H3068"\w* woman came to help Rachel have her baby, but Rachel had \w a|strong="H3068"\w* lot of pain, and she had trouble having that baby.  
\p Then Rachel had her baby, but that pain was really bad. That woman said to her, “Don’t be frightened. You have another son.”   
