\c 36  
\s1 The story about Esau’s family  
\p
\v 1 \w This|strong="H1931"\w* \w is|strong="H1931"\w* \w the|strong="H1931"\w* story about Jacob’s brother \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w and|strong="H6215"\w* \w his|strong="H6215"\w* family. Sometimes \w people|strong="H1931"\w* called \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* different name. \w They|strong="H1931"\w* called \w him|strong="H1931"\w* \em Edom\em*.   
\p
\v 2 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w married|strong="H3947"\w* some \w women|strong="H1323"\w* \w from|strong="H3947"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w* country. \w These|strong="H3947"\w* \w are|strong="H1323"\w* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* names \w of|strong="H1323"\w* those \w women|strong="H1323"\w*,\x * \xo 36:2 \xt Genesis 26:34\x*  
\li1 – Adah. Her father’s name was Elon, and he was from the Heth tribe.  
\li1 – Oholibamah. Her father’s name was Anah. Her grand-father’s name was Zibeyon, and he was from the Hiv tribe.   
\li1
\v 3 – Basemath. Her father’s name was Ishmael, and her brother’s name was Nebayoth.\x * \xo 36:3 \xt Genesis 28:9\x*   
\p
\v 4 All \w of|strong="H3205"\w* those women \w had|strong="H3205"\w* \w sons|strong="H3205"\w* with \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*. \w Adah|strong="H5711"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H3205"\w* called Elifaz, \w Basemath|strong="H1315"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w son|strong="H3205"\w* called Rewel,  
\v 5 \w and|strong="H1121"\w* Oholibamah \w had|strong="H3205"\w* 3 \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* called Jeyush, \w Jalam|strong="H3281"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Korah|strong="H7141"\w*.  
\p \w That|strong="H1121"\w*’s all \w the|strong="H3205"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w that|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w had|strong="H3205"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w they|strong="H3205"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* all \w born|strong="H3205"\w* \w in|strong="H1121"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w* country.   
\p
\v 6-8 Esau and his brother Jacob, they both lived in Canaan country. And Esau and Jacob both had lots and lots of animals. But there was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* problem. There wasn’t enough grass and water in that country for all of Esau’s animals and all of Jacob’s animals.  
\p So Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and everyone else that lived in his camp, and he took all his animals and everything else that he owned, and he left Canaan country. He went to the hill country called Seir, and he set up his camp there. That place was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* long way away from Jacob.  
\p And you know, sometimes people called Esau \w a|strong="H3068"\w* different name. They called him \em Edom\em*.   
\s1 The names of Esau’s sons and grand-sons  
\p
\v 9 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s family \w was|strong="H2022"\w* called \w the|strong="H2022"\w* Edom tribe, \w and|strong="H2022"\w* they lived \w in|strong="H2022"\w* \w the|strong="H2022"\w* \w hill|strong="H2022"\w* \w country|strong="H2022"\w* called \w Seir|strong="H8165"\w*. These \w are|strong="H2022"\w* \w the|strong="H2022"\w* names \w of|strong="H2022"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s sons \w and|strong="H2022"\w* grand-sons.   
\p
\v 10 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s 2 oldest \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Elifaz. His mother’s name was Adah, and she was one of Esau’s wives.  
\li1 – Rewel. His mother’s name was Basemath, and she was another one of Esau’s wives.   
\p
\v 11 These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* names \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Elifaz’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Teman  
\li1 – Omar  
\li1 – Zefo  
\li1 – Gatam  
\li1 – Kenaz   
\m
\v 12 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Elifaz \w had|strong="H1961"\w* another \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w too|strong="H1961"\w*. \w His|strong="H1961"\w* name \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w Amalek|strong="H6002"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* mother’s name \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w Timna|strong="H8555"\w*. \w That|strong="H1121"\w* \w woman|strong="H3205"\w* \w Timna|strong="H8555"\w*, she \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w like|strong="H1961"\w* another wife \w for|strong="H1121"\w* Elifaz.  
\p All \w those|strong="H1121"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* Elifaz’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*. \w They|strong="H3205"\w* \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H3205"\w* grand-sons \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* wife \w Adah|strong="H5711"\w*.   
\p
\v 13 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Rewel \w had|strong="H1961"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w too|strong="H1961"\w*. These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* names \w of|strong="H1121"\w* Rewel’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Nahath  
\li1 – Zerah  
\li1 – Shammah  
\li1 – Mizzah  
\m They \w were|strong="H1961"\w* \w the|strong="H1961"\w* grand-sons \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H1961"\w* wife \w Basemath|strong="H1315"\w*.   
\p
\v 14 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* another wife, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w her|strong="H3205"\w* name \w was|strong="H1961"\w* Oholibamah. \w Her|strong="H3205"\w* \w father|strong="H3205"\w*’s name \w was|strong="H1961"\w* \w Anah|strong="H6034"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w her|strong="H3205"\w* grand-father’s name \w was|strong="H1961"\w* Zibeyon. Oholibamah \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* 3 \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* together. These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H1961"\w* names,  
\li1 – Jeyush  
\li1 – Jalam  
\li1 – Korah   
\s1 The names of clan leaders in Esau’s tribe  
\p
\v 15 \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s tribe split \w up|strong="H1121"\w* into clans, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* all \w those|strong="H1121"\w* clans \w had|strong="H1121"\w* leaders. These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* names \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w those|strong="H1121"\w* leaders.  
\p \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s \w oldest|strong="H1060"\w* \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Elifaz, \w he|strong="H1121"\w* \w had|strong="H1121"\w* these \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Teman  
\li1 – Omar  
\li1 – Zefo  
\li1 – Kenaz   
\li1
\v 16 – Korah  
\li1 – Gatam  
\li1 – Amalek  
\p All \w those|strong="H1121"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* Elifaz’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* they \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H1121"\w* their clans \w in|strong="H1121"\w* Edom country. Their grand-mother \w was|strong="H1121"\w* Esau’s wife \w Adah|strong="H5711"\w*.   
\p
\v 17 These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Rewel,  
\li1 – Nahath  
\li1 – Zerah  
\li1 – Shammah  
\li1 – Mizzah  
\p \w Those|strong="H1121"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* Rewel’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* they \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H1121"\w* \w their|strong="H7467"\w* clans \w in|strong="H1121"\w* Edom country. \w Their|strong="H7467"\w* grand-mother \w was|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s wife \w Basemath|strong="H1315"\w*.   
\p
\v 18 These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s wife Oholibamah,  
\li1 – Jeyush  
\li1 – Jalam  
\li1 – Korah  
\p \w Those|strong="H1121"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* Oholibamah’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* they \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H1121"\w* their clans. Oholibamah’s \w father|strong="H1121"\w* \w was|strong="H1121"\w* called \w Anah|strong="H6034"\w*.   
\p
\v 19 All \w those|strong="H1121"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*, \w they|strong="H1931"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H1121"\w* their clans.  
\p \w And|strong="H1121"\w* you know, sometimes \w people|strong="H1121"\w* called \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* different name. \w They|strong="H1931"\w* called \w him|strong="H1931"\w* \em Edom\em*.   
\s1 The names of clan leaders in the Hor tribe  
\p
\v 20 \w There|strong="H3427"\w* \w was|strong="H1121"\w* another tribe \w living|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H1121"\w* country too. They \w lived|strong="H3427"\w* \w there|strong="H3427"\w* \w before|strong="H3427"\w* Esau’s family came \w there|strong="H3427"\w*. \w That|strong="H1121"\w* tribe \w was|strong="H1121"\w* called \w the|strong="H3427"\w* Hor tribe. \w The|strong="H3427"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H1121"\w* tribe \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3427"\w* \w kids|strong="H1121"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* grand-kids \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w* called \w Seir|strong="H8165"\w*.  
\p These \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3427"\w* names \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Seir|strong="H8165"\w*’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Lotan  
\li1 – Shobal  
\li1 – Zibeyon  
\li1 – Anah   
\li1
\v 21 – Dishon  
\li1 – Ezer  
\li1 – Dishan  
\p All \w those|strong="H1121"\w* \w men|strong="H1121"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w Seir|strong="H8165"\w*’s \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* they \w were|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H1121"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H1121"\w* their clans \w in|strong="H1121"\w* Edom country.   
\p
\v 22 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w Lotan|strong="H3877"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* these \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Hori  
\li1 – Hemam  
\p \w Lotan|strong="H3877"\w* \w also|strong="H1121"\w* \w had|strong="H1961"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* sister called \w Timna|strong="H8555"\w*.   
\p
\v 23 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w Shobal|strong="H7732"\w* \w had|strong="H1121"\w* these \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Alvan  
\li1 – Manahath  
\li1 – Ebal  
\li1 – Shefo  
\li1 – Onam   
\p
\v 24 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Zibeyon \w had|strong="H1121"\w* \w these|strong="H1931"\w* \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Ayah  
\li1 – Anah. (Anah is the man that found springs in the desert. One day, he was out in the desert, and he was looking after some donkeys that belonged to his father Zibeyon. And he found some springs with hot water in them.)   
\p
\v 25 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w Anah|strong="H6034"\w* \w had|strong="H1121"\w* these \w kids|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Dishon  
\li1 – Oholibamah. She was Anah’s daughter.   
\p
\v 26 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Dishon \w had|strong="H1121"\w* these \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Hemdan  
\li1 – Eshban  
\li1 – Ithran  
\li1 – Keran   
\p
\v 27 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* Ezer \w had|strong="H1121"\w* these \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Bilhan  
\li1 – Zavan  
\li1 – Akan   
\p
\v 28 Seir’s \w son|strong="H1121"\w* \w Dishan|strong="H1789"\w* \w had|strong="H1121"\w* these \w sons|strong="H1121"\w*,  
\li1 – Uz  
\li1 – Aran   
\p
\v 29 These are \w the|strong="H7732"\w* names of \w the|strong="H7732"\w* leaders in \w the|strong="H7732"\w* Hor tribe,  
\li1 – Lotan  
\li1 – Shobal  
\li1 – Zibeyon  
\li1 – Anah   
\li1
\v 30 – Dishon  
\li1 – Ezer  
\li1 – Dishan  
\p All those men were in \w the|strong="H8165"\w* Hor tribe, \w and|strong="H1787"\w* they were \w the|strong="H8165"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H8165"\w* their clans in \w the|strong="H8165"\w* country called \w Seir|strong="H8165"\w*.   
\s1 The names of the big bosses in Edom country  
\p
\v 31 \w At|strong="H3478"\w* \w first|strong="H1121"\w*, \w the|strong="H6440"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* mob didn’t \w have|strong="H1121"\w* big bosses \w over|strong="H4427"\w* \w them|strong="H6440"\w*. \w A|strong="H3068"\w* \w long|strong="H6440"\w* \w time|strong="H6440"\w* later, \w they|strong="H3478"\w* started \w having|strong="H4428"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* big boss \w over|strong="H4427"\w* \w them|strong="H6440"\w*. \w But|strong="H4428"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w*, \w the|strong="H6440"\w* Edom mob \w had|strong="H3478"\w* big bosses \w in|strong="H3478"\w* \w their|strong="H6440"\w* country. \w These|strong="H6440"\w* \w are|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H6440"\w* names \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w those|strong="H1121"\w* big bosses \w in|strong="H3478"\w* Edom.   
\p
\v 32 \w The|strong="H8034"\w* 1st big boss \w in|strong="H4427"\w* Edom country, \w his|strong="H4427"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w Bela|strong="H1106"\w*. \w He|strong="H8034"\w* lived \w in|strong="H4427"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w town|strong="H5892"\w* \w called|strong="H8034"\w* \w Dinhabah|strong="H1838"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H4427"\w* \w father|strong="H1121"\w*’s \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w Beor|strong="H1160"\w*.   
\p
\v 33 \w Bela|strong="H1106"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w then|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w* called \w Jobab|strong="H3103"\w* \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* big boss. \w He|strong="H8478"\w* \w was|strong="H1121"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* town called \w Bozrah|strong="H1224"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H8478"\w* \w father|strong="H1121"\w*’s name \w was|strong="H1121"\w* \w Zerah|strong="H2226"\w*.   
\p
\v 34 \w Jobab|strong="H3103"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H4191"\w* \w then|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H4191"\w* called \w Husham|strong="H2367"\w* \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* big boss. \w He|strong="H8478"\w* \w was|strong="H3103"\w* \w from|strong="H8478"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* land \w of|strong="H8478"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* Teman clan.   
\p
\v 35 \w Husham|strong="H2367"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w then|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w* \w called|strong="H8034"\w* \w Hadad|strong="H1908"\w* \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H5221"\w* big boss. \w He|strong="H5221"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w from|strong="H1121"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w town|strong="H5892"\w* \w called|strong="H8034"\w* \w Avith|strong="H5762"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H5221"\w* \w father|strong="H1121"\w*’s \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* Bedad. \w Hadad|strong="H1908"\w* fought \w the|strong="H5221"\w* \w Midian|strong="H4080"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w in|strong="H4191"\w* \w Moab|strong="H4124"\w* \w country|strong="H7704"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w he|strong="H5221"\w* won.   
\p
\v 36 \w Hadad|strong="H1908"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H4191"\w* \w then|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H4191"\w* called \w Samlah|strong="H8072"\w* \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* big boss. \w He|strong="H8478"\w* \w was|strong="H1908"\w* \w from|strong="H8478"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* town called \w Masrekah|strong="H4957"\w*.   
\p
\v 37 \w Samlah|strong="H8072"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H7586"\w* \w then|strong="H7586"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H4191"\w* called Shawl \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* big boss. \w He|strong="H8478"\w* \w was|strong="H7586"\w* \w from|strong="H8478"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* town called \w Rehoboth|strong="H7344"\w*, next \w to|strong="H4191"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* \w river|strong="H5104"\w*.   
\p
\v 38 Shawl \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w then|strong="H7586"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w* called \w Baal-Hanan|strong="H1177"\w* \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* big boss. \w His|strong="H8478"\w* \w father|strong="H1121"\w*’s name \w was|strong="H7586"\w* Akbor.   
\p
\v 39 \w Baal-Hanan|strong="H1177"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w then|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w man|strong="H1121"\w* \w called|strong="H8034"\w* \w Hadad|strong="H1924"\w* \w became|strong="H4427"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* big boss. \w He|strong="H8478"\w* lived \w in|strong="H4191"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w town|strong="H5892"\w* \w called|strong="H8034"\w* \w Pau|strong="H6464"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w his|strong="H8478"\w* wife’s \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w Mehetabel|strong="H4105"\w*. \w She|strong="H5892"\w* \w was|strong="H8034"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* \w daughter|strong="H1323"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Matred|strong="H4308"\w* \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H8478"\w* grand-daughter \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Mezahab|strong="H4314"\w*.   
\s1 The names of clan leaders in Esau’s tribe  
\p
\v 40 \w Some|strong="H4725"\w* \w people|strong="H4940"\w* \w in|strong="H8034"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*’s \w tribe|strong="H4940"\w* \w were|strong="H4940"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H8034"\w* their \w clans|strong="H4940"\w*. \w And|strong="H4725"\w* all those \w clans|strong="H4940"\w* lived \w in|strong="H8034"\w* different \w places|strong="H4725"\w*. These \w are|strong="H8034"\w* \w the|strong="H8034"\w* \w names|strong="H8034"\w* \w of|strong="H8034"\w* those \w clan|strong="H4940"\w* leaders,  
\li1 – Timna  
\li1 – Alvah  
\li1 – Jetheth   
\li1
\v 41 – Oholibamah  
\li1 – Elah  
\li1 – Pinon   
\li1
\v 42 – Kenaz  
\li1 – Teman  
\li1 – Mibzar   
\li1
\v 43 – Magdiel  
\li1 – Iram  
\p \w Those|strong="H1931"\w* \w people|strong="H1931"\w* \w were|strong="H6215"\w* \w the|strong="H1931"\w* leaders \w for|strong="H1931"\w* their clans \w in|strong="H4186"\w* \w the|strong="H1931"\w* Edom tribe. All \w those|strong="H1931"\w* clans \w lived|strong="H4186"\w* \w in|strong="H4186"\w* different \w places|strong="H4186"\w*.  
\p All \w the|strong="H1931"\w* \w people|strong="H1931"\w* \w in|strong="H4186"\w* \w the|strong="H1931"\w* Edom tribe \w were|strong="H6215"\w* \w the|strong="H1931"\w* kids \w and|strong="H6215"\w* grand-kids \w of|strong="H4186"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*.   
\c 37  
\s1 Jacob’s son Joseph had dreams  
\p
\v 1 \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w* \w lived|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w* country. \w That|strong="H3427"\w*’s \w the|strong="H3427"\w* country \w where|strong="H4033"\w* \w his|strong="H3290"\w* father Isaac used \w to|strong="H3427"\w* \w have|strong="H3667"\w* \w his|strong="H3290"\w* camp.   
\p
