\s1 Joseph’s brothers tricked their father Jacob  
\p
\v 31 \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w*’s brothers wanted \w their|strong="H3947"\w* father \w to|strong="H3947"\w* think \w that|strong="H1818"\w* \w an|strong="H3947"\w* animal \w killed|strong="H7819"\w* \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w*. \w So|strong="H3947"\w* \w they|strong="H3947"\w* \w killed|strong="H7819"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w goat|strong="H5795"\w*, \w and|strong="H1818"\w* \w they|strong="H3947"\w* \w got|strong="H3947"\w* some \w of|strong="H1818"\w* \w that|strong="H1818"\w* \w goat|strong="H5795"\w*’s \w blood|strong="H1818"\w*, \w and|strong="H1818"\w* \w they|strong="H3947"\w* \w put|strong="H3947"\w* \w the|strong="H3947"\w* \w blood|strong="H1818"\w* \w on|strong="H5795"\w* \w that|strong="H1818"\w* special \w coat|strong="H3801"\w* \w that|strong="H1818"\w* belonged \w to|strong="H3947"\w* \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w*.  
