\p \w At|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* \w time|strong="H5921"\w*, Tamar \w was|strong="H1931"\w* wearing \w the|strong="H5921"\w* sort \w of|strong="H3427"\w* clothes \w that|strong="H3588"\w* widows wear. \w But|strong="H3588"\w* \w then|strong="H5414"\w*, Tamar changed \w those|strong="H5921"\w* clothes, \w and|strong="H1870"\w* \w she|strong="H1931"\w* \w put|strong="H5414"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* some pretty clothes, \w and|strong="H1870"\w* \w she|strong="H1931"\w* \w put|strong="H5414"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* scarf \w over|strong="H5921"\w* \w her|strong="H5414"\w* head, \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w cover|strong="H3680"\w* \w her|strong="H5414"\w* \w face|strong="H7200"\w*. \w Then|strong="H5414"\w* \w she|strong="H1931"\w* \w went|strong="H5493"\w* \w and|strong="H1870"\w* \w sat|strong="H3427"\w* \w outside|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* town called Enayim. \w That|strong="H3588"\w* town \w is|strong="H1931"\w* \w on|strong="H5921"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* \w road|strong="H1870"\w* \w that|strong="H3588"\w* goes \w to|strong="H5921"\w* \w Timnah|strong="H8553"\w*.   
\p
\v 15-16 Later, Judah walked along that road, and he saw Tamar sitting there. She had that scarf over her head, and Judah couldn’t see her face. So Judah didn’t know that she was Tamar, his dead son’s wife. He thought she was \w a|strong="H3068"\w* woman that sleeps with men for pay. So Judah went to her, and he said, “I want to sleep with you, like \w a|strong="H3068"\w* man sleeps with his wife.”  
\p Tamar said, “If I sleep with you, then you have to give me something to pay me. What will you give me?”   
\p
