\v 21 \w And|strong="H5971"\w* \w Joseph|strong="H5971"\w* got \w all|strong="H5704"\w* \w the|strong="H5704"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* work \w for|strong="H5704"\w* Pharaoh.   
\p
\v 22-26 And Joseph said to the people, “Listen. Today I gave you mob to Pharaoh, to work for him. And I gave him your land as well. Now I will give you seeds to plant in the ground, so that you can grow food plants. Every time you take food from those plants, you have to split up that food into 5 piles, and give one pile to Pharaoh. You can keep the rest of that food for yourselves. Then you and your families and your little kids, and all the people that live in your homes, you will all have food to eat. And you can take some of the seeds from those food plants, and you can plant those seeds in the ground, so that you can keep growing more food plants.”  
\p Then the Egypt people said to Joseph, “Sir, you saved our lives. Thank you for being good to us. We will be Pharaoh’s workers, just like you said.”  
\p So Joseph made \w a|strong="H3068"\w* new law for Egypt country. That law said that every time the Egypt people got food from their food plants, they had to split up that food into 5 piles, and give one pile to Pharaoh. And you know, that law is still there in Egypt country.  
\p After that time, Pharaoh owned all the land in Egypt country. Only the ceremony men still owned their own land. You see, Pharaoh always paid those ceremony men, so they didn’t need to sell him their land to get food. So their land still belonged to them, it didn’t belong to Pharaoh.   
\s1 Jacob told Joseph to bury his body in Canaan country  
\p
\v 27 \w At|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w* \w time|strong="H3478"\w*, Jacob \w and|strong="H3478"\w* \w his|strong="H3478"\w* family started \w to|strong="H3478"\w* \w live|strong="H3427"\w* \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w* country, \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H3427"\w* \w place|strong="H3427"\w* called \w Goshen|strong="H1657"\w*. \w They|strong="H3478"\w* got \w their|strong="H3427"\w* own land \w in|strong="H3427"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w* \w place|strong="H3427"\w*, \w and|strong="H3478"\w* lots \w more|strong="H7235"\w* kids \w were|strong="H3478"\w* born \w into|strong="H4714"\w* \w their|strong="H3427"\w* family, \w so|strong="H3966"\w* \w that|strong="H3478"\w* \w they|strong="H3478"\w* \w became|strong="H7235"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w really|strong="H3966"\w* big mob \w of|strong="H3427"\w* \w people|strong="H3427"\w*.   
\p
