\s1 Jacob made Ephraim more important than Manasseh  
\p
\v 8-10 Jacob was very old, and his eyes were weak, so he couldn’t see very well. He looked at Joseph’s 2 sons, and he said to Joseph, “Who are these 2 boys?”  
\p Joseph said, “They are my sons, the ones that God gave me here in this country.”  
\p Then Jacob said, “Bring them near to me. I will put my hands on them, and I will ask God to be good to them.”  
\p So Joseph took his 2 sons near to Jacob. And Jacob hugged those 2 boys, and he kissed them on their cheeks.  
