\p
\v 26 \w Then|strong="H4191"\w* \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w* \w died|strong="H4191"\w*. \w He|strong="H8141"\w* \w was|strong="H1121"\w* 110 \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w old|strong="H1121"\w*. \w The|strong="H4191"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w* \w people|strong="H1121"\w* \w put|strong="H4191"\w* special oils \w and|strong="H3967"\w* perfumes \w on|strong="H4191"\w* \w Joseph|strong="H3130"\w*’s \w body|strong="H4191"\w*, \w so|strong="H4191"\w* \w that|strong="H8141"\w* \w it|strong="H4191"\w* \w will|strong="H4714"\w* \w not|strong="H4191"\w* rot away. \w Then|strong="H4191"\w* \w they|strong="H8141"\w* wrapped \w his|strong="H4191"\w* \w body|strong="H4191"\w* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w long|strong="H8141"\w* bits \w of|strong="H1121"\w* cloth, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w they|strong="H8141"\w* \w put|strong="H4191"\w* \w it|strong="H4191"\w* \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* coffin \w in|strong="H8141"\w* \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w* country.   
\b  
\iex (We have not yet translated the books called Exodus, Leviticus, Numbers, Deuteronomy, Joshua, Judges, and Ruth. Some of the stories in those books tell us these things.  
\iex – Jacob’s family lived in Egypt for about 400 years, and became the nation called Israel. The families that came from his 12 sons became the 12 tribes in the Israel nation.  
\iex – Then God got an Israel man, called Moses, to take the Israel nation out of Egypt, into desert country, and God gave Moses his law for those people.  
\iex – After that, God gave them the country called Canaan. Today we call that country Israel. Sometimes we call the Israel people the \em Jewish\em* people, or just the \em Jews\em*.)  